        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 2 at 3:35PM CDT until April 2 at 3:45PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Beason to near Cornland, moving northeast at 60
mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Emergency management. A 70 mph wind gust was reported in
Elkhart at 324 pm.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
considerable tree damage. Wind damage is also likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

These severe storms will be near...
Mount Pulaski, Beason, and Chestnut around 340 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include
Broadwell.

This includes Interstate 55 near mile marker 119.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for central
Illinois.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Prepare immediately for large hail and deadly cloud to ground
lightning. Seek shelter inside a well-built structure. Stay away from
windows.</instruction>
